[05:36.35]KENT	Most certain, sir.
[05:38.21]Gentleman	Who is conductor of his people?
[05:41.20]KENT	As 'tis said, the bastard son of Gloucester.
[05:45.08]Gentleman	They say Edgar, his banished son, is with the Earl
[05:49.53]	of Kent in Germany.
[05:51.55]KENT	Report is changeable. 'Tis time to look about; the
[05:55.91]	powers of the kingdom approach apace.
[05:59.39]Gentleman	The arbitrement is like to be bloody. Fare you
[06:03.59]	well, sir.
[06:04.81]	[Exit]
[06:05.78]KENT	My point and period will be throughly wrought,
[06:09.98]	Or well or ill, as this day's battle's fought.
[06:14.11]	[Exit]
